SNS: Simple notification service:
---------------------------------

SNS is a fully managed messaging service from AWS.
SNS used to send notifications and messages between applications, users and systems.

SNS helps one system publish a message, and many receivers can subscribe to get that message instantly

Example:
--------
If an order is placed on a shopping website,
SNS can notify:
  -customers by email/SMS
  -Billing system
  -Inventory system
  -Delivery team

HOW SNS Works: (Core components)
---------------------------------
1. Topic
-A communication channel where messages are sent
Ex: OrderPlacedTopic

2.Publisher
-The sender that publishes message to topic
Ex: EC2 app, Lambda, cloudwatch alarm

3.Subscriber
-Receivers who get messages from topic

Subscribers can be:
-Email
-SMS
-HTTP/HTTPS endpoint

Architecture Flow:
------------------
APP/Service ------> SNS Topic -----> Multiple subscribers

Real AWS Example:
-----------------
-Amazon Cloudwatch detects CPU>90%
-Sends alert to SNS Topic
-SNS sends: Email to Admin, SMS to Engineers

Benefits:
---------
-Fully managed
-Scalable
-Highly available
-pay as you use
-Fast message delivery

Common Use Cases:
-----------------
-Alerts and Monitoring
-Application notifications
-Fan-out messaging






















